{
  "texts": [
    "The loss function for our VAE model is as follows:",
    "where BCEðx; xÞ is the binary cross-entropy between the input expression data x and the reconstructed expression data x.",
    "The term D KL ðNðμ; σ 2 ÞjjNð0; IÞÞ is the KullbackLeibler (KL) divergence 60 between the estimated posterior distribution Nðμ; σ 2 Þ and the prior distribution Nð0; IÞ.",
    "The term kθ 1 k 2 is the L 2 -norm of the learnable parameters in KL-PMVAE and λ 1 is the regularization parameter that can be tuned to control the severity of the penalization.",
    "The value of β controls how much emphasis should be placed on the KL-divergence term of the loss function and is set to 1 in conventional VAE but will be changed gradually from 0 to 1 in a KL-annealing learning scheme as described below."
  ]
}